Machine Learning Model
-----> PYTHON
-----> Editor[VIM, VsCode, pycharm, DataSpell,etc]
-----> libraries : sklearn, pandas, plotly

i) Direct Install on Laptop (5-10%)
pro:
	easy to setup!
con:
    a) NOT PORTABLE

(20-30%)
ii) Virtual environment on my laptop using Python
pro:
	isolated setup for each project ON THE SAME LAPTOP!
con:
	a)space might be wasted due to install of similar versions
	of softwares

	b)NOT PORTABLE!


[spoilt for choices]

iii) VM machine can be setup

pro:
	a)separation of an entire environment!
	b) VM IMAGE CAN BE PORTED TO A DIFFERENT system
con:
	a) system will be slow to boot
	b) space wastage is a lot!

iv) Use a development container based on Docker engine


pro:
	
	i) Reuse base OS (HOST OS) environment can be reused
	across separate containers
	ii) portability is GREAT!
	iii) can be started and stopped quickly!
	
con:
	
	
	i) Cannot be used for virtualizing GUI applications*.
	ii)still requires a middle layer (ENGINE)



	rocket, podman, docker, etc!



